[3
Date: Tue, 26 May 1998 14:33:16 -0400
From: fleishe1@ix.netcom.com

I have my doubts about the reliability of the estimates stated. Most
foodborne illness are self limiting and do not get reported to any
surveillance system. Further, in many cases, medical attention is not
sought due to the self-limited nature of the illnesses.
What we had was a discussion of reported outbreaks not all foodborne
illness in the U.S. and thus no more than a gross under-estimate with
limited validity. Am I missing something here?
--
